strings: <Cap><leader> discovers a new recipe for the alchemy pot!
<Cap><string_1> <equal> <Cap><string_2> + <Cap><string_3>
<Cap><string_1> <equal> <Cap><string_2> + <Cap><string_3> + <Cap><string_4>
<se_low>*: Who are you!? This place 'ere belongs to the great thief, Red.
<se_low>*: I dunno wot it is ya want, but Red don't take kindly to visitors when she's 'avin' a rest. So clear off!
<se_low>*: Well, if it ain't Yangus! Wot d'ya think you're doin' 'ere, eh?
<se_low>*: Red'll skin yer alive if she catches ya. So clear off! You ain't welcome round 'ere!
<se_def>*: It's a cryin' shame to have a stable but no 'orses to go inside. I wish Red'd do somefin' about it.
<se_def>*: Isn't she a beauty!? You won't find another coat like that within an 'undred miles o' Pickham.<page>*: She must've been brought up on some mighty fine grub.
<se_def>*: Red knows quality when she sees it. She only buys the best!
Princess Medea is fettered at the ankle.
<se_low>*: Red's waitin' for ya inside. Hurry up!
<se_low>*: There ain't no way you're gonna be able to get that Venus' tear. Even Red couldn't manage it.
<se_low>*: But go ahead an' do yer worst! I won't be 'oldin' me breath!
<se_low>*: Wot d'you want!? This 'ere's the residence o' the great thief, Red.
<se_low>*: I dunno wot yer doin' 'ere, but Red don't take kindly to visitors when she's 'avin' a rest. So clear off!
<se_high>Red: Bring me the Venus' tear from the cave up north and I'll think about givin' you back your precious 'orse.
<se_high>Red: ‘Venus' tear’. Mm, sounds like a quality name, don't ya think? Yeah, it must be quite a jewel.
<se_low>*: You wot!? Ya got it!? I don't believe it! So it's the real deal then, that Venus' tear?
<se_low>*: Crikey! I was sure <IF_SOLO>you<ELSE_NOT_SOLO>you lot<ENDIF_SOLO> was gonna give up an' do a runner. There's more to ya than I thought.
<se_high>Red: Wot? You've got the Venus' tear? Good for you! But it was Yangus I 'ad an agreement with.
<se_high>Red: I'm only talkin' to 'im. Otherwise the deal's off!
<se_high>Red: Listen, you can do wot ya want with the 'orse, but we're done 'ere, right? So get out!
<se_low>*: Go on! I ain't gonna stand in yer way after wot you pulled off the other day.
<se_low>*: An' anyway, Red'll be 'appy to see ya, I reckon. She wouldn't tell ya so 'erself, mind.
<se_def>*: That 'orse of yours is a fine animal. I'd be 'appy as Larry if I 'ad a mare like that.
<se_def>*: I 'ope Red'll get 'old of another one from somewhere. Must cost a bit though, eh?
<se_high>Red: Oh, it's you again. D'ya like thieves' hideouts or somethin'?
<se_high>Red: Well seein' as yer 'ere, you can pass on a message to Yangus for me.
<se_high>Red: Tell 'im I don't ever wanna see 'is grubby face 'round 'ere again! Okay?
<se_high>Red: You just keep turnin' up like a bad penny, don't ya!? Wot the 'ell d'ya want this time, eh?
<se_low>Yangus: ...I was just thinkin' ya might be lonely, is all. Thought I'd drop in an' see 'ow ya was.
<se_high>Red: You tryin' to chat me up or somefin'!?
<se_high>Red: I've 'ad it up to 'ere wiv your rubbish! Get out of 'ere! Sort yerself out!
<se_low>*: You <IF_SOLO><ELSE_NOT_SOLO>lot <ENDIF_SOLO>again!? D'ya fancy Red or somefin'!?
<se_low>*: Oh, right. Yer lookin' for somefin'. Wotever.
<se_high>Red: Back AGAIN!? This isn't some kids' playground, you know! Ya bloomin' weirdo.
<se_high>Red: So tell me. How's Yangus doin'?
<se_high>Red: Causin' you a load of grief, I suppose. I'm tellin' ya, that man's a waste o' space!
<se_high>Red: I've never seen or 'eard of a Moonshadow 'arp. You'll 'ave to try somewhere else.
<se_high>Red: I thought it might be nice to see ya again, seein' as it's been a while an' all.<page>Red: But yer just 'ere to ask for information! Talk about a cheek!
<se_low>*: Red ain't just a beautiful lady, she's one 'ell of a thief an' all. It's an 'onour to serve 'er.
<se_high>Red: Wot are you doin' 'ere again? This ain't an open 'ouse, you know.
<se_high>Red: So, 'ow are you gettin' on with Yangus, then?
<se_high>Red: No doubt he's causing you a load of trouble. I dunno why anyone would bother with a man like that.
<se_high>Red: The Moonshadow harp, eh? Must be worth somethin'. Not a bad job for you, Yangus.
<se_high>Red: I don't really go in for small jobs myself, though.
<se_low>*: Well, well! Yer back again, eh? This place ain't exactly on the way to anywhere, so we don't get no other visitors.
<se_low>*: I'm actually startin' to look forward to you comin' by.
<se_low>*: Uh-oh! Red'll kill me if she 'ears me sayin' stuff like that. Don't tell 'er! I ain't s'posed to be friendly.
<se_high>Red: The wanderers return. But this isn't your home, you know! Wot are ya doin' 'ere!?
<se_high>Red: And 'ow's Yangus gettin' on?
<se_high>Red: I bet you've just about 'ad enough of 'im by now, 'aven't you? He's more trouble than 'e's worth, that bloke!
<se_high>Red: I don't know wot kind of boat you've got yerself, but it won't stack up against the Classy Lady. She's the finest vessel on the seas!
<se_high>Red: I burnt a lot of dough to get 'er, I did. Maybe I'll show 'er to ya some day.
<se_high>Red: Back again, are ya? This isn't some kids' playground, ya know! Yer a bit of a freak really, aren't ya?
<se_high>Red: So, then. How's Yangus?
<se_high>Red: No doubt causin' you all kinds o' trouble. You wanna watch 'im!
<se_high>Red: How many times 'ave I told ya to clear off, eh? But you still keep comin' back, don't you, you doughnut!
<se_high>Red: Ever since you've 'ooked up wiv those blokes yer travellin' wiv, you've changed.
<se_low>Yangus: Changed? How's that then?
<se_high>Red: Just look at yer face! You've lost yer oomph! There's not an 'int of the old Yangus left in ya!
<se_high>Red: Wot's 'appened to ya, eh?
<se_high>Red: You used to have a nice mean look in yer eyes. A crook's face. You USED to look like a man!
<se_high>Red: But now... Well, I s'pose you are a bit easier to get on with.
<se_def>*: Well that's a shame! Ya come all this way an' Red ain't 'ere. She's gone off on business.
<se_def>*: She was talkin' about goin' to look for some pirate's treasure or somefin'. Captain Grow, was it? Nah, Captain Fro's treasure, maybe?
<se_def>*: Anyway, she took 'er ship an' a load o' supplies, so I don't think she'll be back for a while.
<se_low>*: Awright? How's it goin'? So tell me, wot in the name of Neos 'appened down in that pirate's cave, eh?
<se_low>*: After she got back 'ere off the boat, Red said she was gonna be goin' away travellin' wiv <IF_SOLO>ya<ELSE_NOT_SOLO>you lot<ENDIF_SOLO> for a while, right?
<se_low>*: I don't get it, I don't. One's company, two's a crowd for 'er. Wot's goin' on?
<se_low>*: Oi, Yangus, wot in the name of Neos 'appened wiv Red down in that pirate's cave, eh?
<se_low>*: She said she's gonna be goin' off wiv you lot travellin' or somefin'. While I'm stuck 'ere like a lemon lookin' after this gaff!
<se_def>*: I was bored out of me bloomin' brain left 'ere to look after the place all on me own.
<se_def>*: I'm gonna 'ave to get Red to buy me an 'orse or I'm gonna go stark ravin' bonkers.
<se_def>*: But she's goin' off travellin' wiv <IF_SOLO>you<ELSE_NOT_SOLO>you lot<ENDIF_SOLO> now, so I guess it'll 'ave to wait 'til she gets back.
<se_high>Red: No Yangus, eh? ...I made a bit of a fool of myself down in that cave, didn't I?
<se_high>Red: Must be losin' me touch gettin' knocked out by a pathetic ghost like that Captain Crow.
<se_high>Red: Anyway...thanks for 'elpin' me out.
<se_high>Red: I'm glad it's you 'ere and not 'im. I couldn't 'ave brought meself to say thanks to Yangus.
<se_high>Red: Tsk! Back again? Wot is it this time? Come to gloat 'ave ya?
<se_low>Yangus: ...No, I ain't. Just wanted to check you got back awright. You know, bein' a single bird on yer own an' all.
<se_high>Red: Are you takin' the biscuit!? That's it! Get the 'ell outta 'ere! I don't wanna see yer face round 'ere no more!
<se_high>Red: I said get outta 'ere! Yer really windin' me up now!
<se_high>Red: You've got a bleedin' talent for it!
<se_high>Red: Wot are you doin' back 'ere again? I'll 'ave to start chargin' ya soon.
<se_high>Red: So, 'ow's Yangus doin'?
<se_high>Red: He'll get ya into trouble if yer not careful. You wanna watch 'im.
<se_high>Red: Wot's 'appened to the old Yangus oomph, eh?
<se_high>Red: You used to have a nice mean look in yer eyes. A crook's face. You USED to look like a man!
<se_high>Red: But now... Well, I s'pose you are a bit easier to get on with, at least.
<se_high>Red: No Yangus, eh? ...I made a bit of a fool of myself down in that cave, didn't I?
<se_high>Red: Must be losin' me touch gettin' knocked out by a pathetic ghost like that Captain Crow.
<se_high>Red: Anyway...thanks for 'elpin' me out.
<se_high>Red: I'm glad it's you 'ere and not 'im. I couldn't 'ave brought myself to say thanks to Yangus.

<se_low>*: There you are! So 'ow's Red then?
She's not injured or nuffin', I 'ope?
<se_low>*: I can't stop worryin' all the while that somefin' might 'ave 'appened to 'er.
<se_low>*: Always a pleasure to welcome the 'eroes of this world! Take it easy 'ere for a while, won't ya?
<se_low>*: It's been pretty lonely stuck out 'ere lookin' after the place, I can tell ya. Just me an' 'im on our own.
<se_def>*: I don't give a monkey's uncle about 'ow red the sky is. All I care about's how soon Red's gonna get me an 'orse.
<se_def>*: If I don't get somefin' to do soon, I'm gonna lose me marbles.
<se_high>Red: The 'ole world's gone nuts wiv all of Rhapthorne's messin' about, but if you ask me, the worst is still to come.
<se_high>Red: That's why you've gotta make the most of times like this, I say. Put yer feet up when you can, and get yer oomph back.

<se_high>Red: So, wot ya plannin' to do wiv Yangus, eh?
You can always dump 'im 'ere if yer worried
'e'll slow ya down, ya know.
<se_high>Red: Ahh, it ain't 'alf good to be 'ome. I feel like I can finally relax...
<se_high>Red: <IF_SOLO>You<ELSE_NOT_SOLO>You lot<ENDIF_SOLO> can 'ang about 'ere an' all if ya want to. Seein' as 'ow we're kind of on the same side now and ev'ryfin'.
